attribute.Name: NV_DRIVE_CHECK_IGNORE
attribute.Description: When this property is set to true, the conceptchecker check check net driver will not be applied to the net, used by the CC2 check 'Check Net Driver'

attribute.Name: NV_NET_CONVENTION_IGNORE
attribute.Description: This property when set to true will have the effect of net convention check not applied for the net, use by the CC2 check 'Check Net Convention'

attribute.Name: NV_TEMP_LIMIT_MAX
attribute.Description: This value when set will be used to check against the maximum allowed temperature for a component, used by the CC2 check 'Check temperature range'

attribute.Name: NV_NC_PIN_IGNORE
attribute.Description: When this property is set to true, the conceptchecker check check NC pin will not be applied to the pin, used by the CC2 check 'Check NC pin'

attribute.Name: NV_SNN_IGNORE
attribute.Description: When this property is set to true, the conceptchecker check for single node net will not be applied to the net, used by the CC2 check 'Check Single Node Net'

attribute.Name: NV_NET_LOAD_THRESHOLD
attribute.Description: This value is supplied to over ride the default value of the load threshold for a net, when the load check is run, used by the CC2 check 'Check Load'

attribute.Name: NV_RATING_THRESHOLD
attribute.Description: This value is supplied to over ride the default value of the rating threshold for a component

attribute.Name: DIENOISEMARGINHIGH_ACTUAL
attribute.Description: Minimum voltage in High state at Die Pad - Vihmin

attribute.Name: DIENOISEMARGINLOW_ACTUAL
attribute.Description: Vilmax - Maximum voltage in Low state at Die Pad

attribute.Name: DIEOVERSHOOTHIGH_ACTUAL
attribute.Description: Maximum voltage in High state at DiePad

attribute.Name: DIEOVERSHOOTLOW_ACTUAL
attribute.Description: Minimum voltage in Low state at Die Pad

attribute.Name: DIESETTLETIMEFALL_ACTUAL
attribute.Description: Last time below Vilmax at Die Pad

attribute.Name: DIESETTLETIMERISE_ACTUAL
attribute.Description: Last time above Vihmin at Die Pad

attribute.Name: NV_MLCC_THRESHOLD
attribute.Description: This value will define the minimum voltage level to check for the MLCC component check
